cylindrical shape with hole through the neutron path
where the sample was placed in the center of the
cylinder. The detector contains 20 liters of NaI(Tl)
divided into 16 optically isolated segments. Both the

The 57 MeV electrons were directed at the
Bare Bounce Target in this experiment. The Bare
Bounce Target is made of tantalum plates and a 2.54
cm-thick polyethylene moderatorand was developed to
enhance the epithermal neutron production. A B4C
